                <p>Nestled in the southwest quadrant of Calgary, atop a hill, is the small, close-knit, and upscale neighbourhood of Britannia. This gorgeous, close-to-nature community with beautiful landscapes is one of Calgary's wealthiest neighbourhoods. Splendid houses with elegant architecture – most dating back to as early as the late 1950s dot the beautiful landscapes of this small yet exclusive community. The spectacular Elbow River on the east offers residents magnificent views from their windows and balconies.</p>
                <p>Britannia is also a mature, well-established neighbourhood, meaning residents don't have to travel far to the community's various amenities. Thick vegetation with some trees dating back to the early 1900s offers homes excellent privacy and shade during the warm summer months.</p>
                <p>True to its very British name, the neighbourhood has a British theme that is evident as you make your way through the community. Streets have names like Edinburgh Boulevard, Coronation Drive, and Elizabeth Road. The landscape and architecture in the community boast British styles.</p>
