            <div class="x6 last">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Lakes &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>The Elbow River gently winds along just off Britannia's western border, running through Sandy Beach Park and Riverdale Park – home to a wide variety of activities for the entire family. Britannia's residents also have easy access to the Elbow River pathway system.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Golf &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>The Calgary Golf & Country Club is Britannia's answer to golf lovers. Britannia houses the entrance of this premier golf club established in 1897, which is also one of Calgary's best golf courses.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Crescent Park is Britannia's fun park for children, fully equipped with a playground and a rock wall.</p>
                    <p>Britannia Slopes is a lovely dog park on Britannia Drive SW. The park offers beautiful views of the river and is a fantastic place to get some exercise with your four-legged friend.</p>
                    <p>Riverdale Park is on the ridge above Sandy Beach and has an expansive off-leash area. The park is fantastic for families too and is often a meeting place for various outdoor activities.</p>
                    <p>The Britannia Off-Leash and off-leash fenced-in areas are located side by side along the community's northwest border. They are both fantastic places to let your furry friends off their leashes to romp around with their doggy friends.</p>
                    <p>Stanley Park is a 21-hectare riverfront family park with a variety of features like picnic tables, a swimming pool, playground, baseball and tennis facilities, and even a BBQ grill. With the Elbow River running through the park, it's the perfect destination for a quiet, tranquil, and scenic walk.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Britannia Plaza Shopping Centre is a small shopping mall offering a wide range of exclusive, independent stores owned by local entrepreneurs. It also has over 15 brand name stores and stores for jewelry, home and cookware, technology, books, groceries, wine and spirits, and professional services. Some shops and services to check out here are:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Ginger Laurier – for fashion and shoes.</li>
                        <li>The Tech Shop – for running and walking shoes.</li>
                        <li>Britannia Kitchen & Home – for distinctive homewares.</li>
                        <li>Owls' Nest Books – for a wide range of books.</li>
                        <li>Bon-A-Pet-Treat for pet food and more.</li>
                        <li>Sunterra Market – for groceries</li>
                        <li>Britannia Wine Merchants – for wine and spirits</li>
                        <li>Village Ice Cream – for ice cream.</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Some professional services here are Britannia Dermedics, Britannia Hair Company & Esthetics, Britannia Medical Clinic, and Chinook Optical.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Fitness &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Lagree YYC is a fitness center located on Elbow Drive SW, offering fantastic workouts by professional instructors.</p>
                    <p>Orangetheory Fitness is an established gym in the area on Elbow Drive SW. Fantastic staff and coaches and intense workouts ensure you see excellent results quickly.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Restaurants and bars &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>A1 Cantina is a Mexican restaurant in Britannia Plaza Shopping Centre offering delicious and authentic Mexican food in a funky ambience. The restaurant is known for its tacos.</p>
                    <p>Monogram Coffee and Starbucks in Britannia Plaza are regular hangouts for those who want to grab a quick espresso before heading off to explore the mall.</p>
                    <p>Village Ice Cream has an incredibly delicious range of ice cream flavours.</p>
                    <p>Britannia's must-try restaurants include Brown's Social House – an upscale fine-dining restaurant, and Suzette Bistro for fresh crêpes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div><!-- Britannia Amenities -->

    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>General feel and vibe &mdash; What's it like living in Britannia?</h2>
        <p>Britannia is a tranquil, family-oriented neighbourhood housing some of Calgary's most luxurious properties. The area offers residents spectacular views of the river and the city. It's the perfect neighbourhood for older couples looking to lead a quiet, small-town life away from the humdrum of city life. The community treasures its green spaces and pathways.</p>
        <div>
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Avenue Magazine Rankings</h3>
            <p>Britannia ranked 109 in Avenue Calgary's list of the most desirable neighbourhoods (2020).</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Overall rank for Best Neighbourhoods 2020: 109</li>
                <li>Restaurant access points: 11</li>
                <li>Public recreation facility access points: 26</li>
                <li>Parks and green space points: 11</li>
                <li>Pathway points: 13</li>
                <li>Walk score: 45</li>
                <li>Transit score: 45</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div><!-- Britannia Feel and Vibe -->

    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>Interesting Facts about Britannia</h2>
        <div>
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Schools In or Near Britannia</h3>
            <p>Britannia is a part of a community of assigned public, catholic, and public schools.</p>
            <h4>Public Schools</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Elboya School (kindergarten, elementary, middle, high)</li>
