        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>According to the 2016 Census of Calgary statistics, 725 people were living in Britannia that year, and today, that number remains more or less the same. The community comprises a large population (nearly 20%) of children aged between 0 and 14. There is a significant population (about 15%) of seniors above 65. Owners occupy around 80% of the houses, and the rest are rented out.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Britannia's real estate is an eclectic mix of charming, mid-century family bungalows, modern, efficient, and elegant single-family homes, and some practical yet tasteful and sophisticated multi-unit condominiums. You can find massive plots that house magazine cover-worthy homes and smaller homes on smaller plots.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Developer/builder/history</h3>
            <p>Britannia became a part of Calgary way back in 1910, but only years later, in 1956, the housing market was developed here. Most of the development in the area took place in the 1950s.</p>
        </div>
    </div><!-- Britannia Facts -->

