    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>FAQs about Britannia Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Is there a pool in the area?</h3>
                <p>Britannia has an outdoor pool housed in Stanley Park. Residents can use the pool during the summer months when it is open.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>What is the crime like in Britannia? Is this a safe neighbourhood?</h3>
                <p>Britannia is safer than 94% of cities in Alberta, and the year-over-year crime here has decreased by 17%. Most crimes are related to car-related thefts and vandalism, and violent crimes are very few – 69% less than the country's average. You have a rare (1 in 60) chance of becoming a victim of crime here. The nearest police facility and fire station are less than two kilometres away, giving residents peace of mind.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Which is the best restaurant in the neighbourhood?</h3>
                <p>Brown's Social House restaurant and bar on Elbow Drive is worth mentioning for a unique blend of two-handed burgers and hand-crafted cocktails in a wonderfully social atmosphere. The menu includes various types of food, including soups and salads, burgers, steaks, brunch, a kid's menu, and house-made desserts.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How do I get around the neighbourhood?</h3>
                <p>Britannia is a car-dependant neighbourhood, and most errands will require a car drive. It is somewhat bikeable, with some bike infrastructure. Some public transport is available for those who prefer the bus or train and a variety of taxi and ride-share companies service the area.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Where can I buy groceries?</h3>
                <p>Head to Sunterra Market in Britannia Plaza for all your groceries requirements. The market is one of the city's famous local markets and is the best place to buy everything you need for your dinner and entertainment requirements. It has a fantastic deli selection, a wide range of cheeses, desserts, and even locally made products.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </div><!-- Britannia FAQs -->

